Question: How to make a POST request with JSON body in Android: :I'm trying to make a POST request with JSON body in Android. I've tried using HttpURLConnection but it's not working. Here is my code:
public void postData() {
    try {
        URL url = new URL("http://mywebsite.com/api/");
        HttpURLConnection conn = (HttpURLConnection) url.openConnection();
        conn.setReadTimeout(10000);
        conn.setConnectTimeout(15000);
        conn.setRequestMethod("POST");
        conn.setDoInput(true);
        conn.setDoOutput(true);
        conn.setRequestProperty("Content-Type", "application/json");

        String jsonBody = "{\"username\":\"myusername\",\"password\":\"mypassword\"}";

        OutputStream os = conn.getOutputStream();
        os.write(jsonBody.getBytes());
        os.flush();

        if (conn.getResponseCode() != HttpURLConnection.HTTP_CREATED) {
            throw new RuntimeException("Failed : HTTP error code : "
                    + conn.getResponseCode());
        }

        BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(
                (conn.getInputStream())));

        String output;
        System.out.println("Output from Server .... \n");
        while ((output = br.readLine()) != null) {
            System.out.println(output);
        }

        conn.disconnect();

    } catch (MalformedURLException e) {
        e.printStackTrace();
    } catch (IOException e) {
        e.printStackTrace();
    }
}

Answer:<<<api>>>: HttpURLConnection
<<<code>>>: HttpURLConnection conn = (HttpURLConnection) url.openConnection();
conn.setRequestMethod("POST");
conn.setRequestProperty("Content-Type", "application/json");
conn.setRequestProperty("Accept", "application/json");
conn.setDoOutput(true);
try(DataOutputStream wr = new DataOutputStream(conn.getOutputStream())) {
    String jsonBody = "{\"username\":\"myusername\",\"password\":\"mypassword\"}";
    wr.writeBytes(jsonBody);
}
conn.connect();
if(conn.getResponseCode() != 200) {
    throw new RuntimeException("Failed : HTTP error code : "
            + conn.getResponseCode());
}
BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(
        (conn.getInputStream())));
String output;
System.out.println("Output from Server .... \n");
while ((output = br.readLine()) != null) {
    System.out.println(output);
}
<<<explanation>>>: HttpURLConnection is a low-level API for making HTTP requests. It's a bit more verbose than using libraries like OkHttp or Retrofit, but it gives you more control over the request and response. In your code, you're setting the request method to "POST", setting the content type to "application/json", and writing the JSON body to the output stream. Then you're reading the response from the server.
